Function Documentation

void RadioDriver_Calibrate (  )

Starts a calibration cycle of the three things that need calibration. See data sheet pages 120 - 122 for details.

void RadioDriver_DisableReceiveMode (  )

Switch to idle mode. Only relevant in non auto rx mode! See configuration define RADIODRIVER_AUTO_RX. It's safe to call this function even if the transceiver is already in idle mode. When a frame is received an action equivalent to calling this function is performed.

void RadioDriver_EnableReceiveMode (  )

Switch to receive mode. Only relevant in non auto rx mode! See configuration define RADIODRIVER_AUTO_RX. It's safe to call this function even if the transceiver is already in receive mode. When a frame has been received the transmitter switches back to non rx mode and EnableReceiveMode must be called again to receive a new frame.

uint8_t RadioDriver_GetRandomNumber (  )

Return a 2 bit random number. A new value is available every 2 us.

void RadioDriver_SetBitRate ( uint8_t  bitRate )

Set transceiver bit rate. Use one of the RADIODRIVER_BITRATE_<bitrate>_KBPS constants.

void RadioDriver_SetReceiverSensitivityThreshold ( uint8_t  level )

Set the threshold below which to ignore frames. Use one of the RADIODRIVER_RECEIVER_SENSITIVITY_THRESHOLD_X_DBM constants. Default value is to receive all frames regardless of RSSI level of their header.

void RadioDriver_WaitForSendToComplete (  )

Waits for a previously initiated send operation to complete.
